Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.38,0:00:06.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know there's an awesome\Ntreasure at the end of this sea?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.61,0:00:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And whoever gets it can be King\Nof the Pirates! Isn't that exciting?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.18,0:00:16.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unheard-of adventures are waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.39,0:00:24.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bon voyage! Let that shred of courage grow
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.26,0:00:31.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I caught a glimpse of\Nthe tail end to the future
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.90,0:00:39.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The horizons everyone\Ndreamed of were separate at first
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.68,0:00:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but now they can be seen\Nthrough a single telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.82,0:00:54.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A bitter compass of destiny\Nis leading your heart astray
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.16,0:00:59.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so turn the wheel in the other direction!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.06,0:01:01.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bon voyage!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.13,0:01:06.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toss aside your bonds and your past
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.37,0:01:13.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can surely smile despite that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.38,0:01:21.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tears shed trying to achieve\Nyour dreams aren't for naught
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.86,0:01:28.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Precious in my life
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.26,0:01:36.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I caught a glimpse of\Nthe tail end to the future
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.21,0:01:56.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,While God Eneru was busy dealing\Nwith Sanji's last-ditch efforts...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.56,0:02:07.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Usopp succeeded in rescuing Sanji.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.13,0:02:11.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meanwhile, Luffy's group...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.54,0:02:14.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...headed up Giant Jack to\Nsettle the score with God Eneru.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.91,0:02:14.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robin! Eneru's after the gold bell, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.91,0:02:17.89,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Gyaaaaa!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.91,0:02:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's at the top of this vine, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.39,0:02:29.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They had but a mere\Nmoment to enjoy their reunion,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.22,0:02:36.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for God Eneru, after repairing\Nthe Maxim, took action again!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.20,0:02:44.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mamaragan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.71,0:02:55.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone! Hurry to the ship!\NI'll get Luffy and bring him back!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.28,0:02:57.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An exquisite view!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.12,0:03:03.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't assume things are gonna\Nturn out how you want, Eneru!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.49,0:03:06.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! He isn't holding back!\NWe gotta get outta here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.93,0:03:14.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything's done for!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.77,0:03:22.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that where the detestable\NShandoran warriors' hidden village is?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.04,0:03:30.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're originally from the Blue Sea;\Nsurely they'd enjoy going home!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.82,0:03:39.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then! Strike the world below!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.83,0:03:48.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our village!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.47,0:03:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was close! We'd be ashes\Nnow had we left any later!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.51,0:04:06.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the name of Great Warrior Calgara...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.99,0:04:14.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...light the fire of Shandora!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.86,0:04:19.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wyper.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.03,0:04:22.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your distant ancestor,\NGreat Warrior Calgara,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.87,0:04:27.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,had another reason for being so\Ndetermined to take back our homeland.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.01,0:04:30.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.61,0:04:36.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It was Calgara's greatest regret of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.35,0:04:41.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen. Great Warrior Calgara\Nhad a very close friend...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.89,0:04:45.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A close friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.22,0:04:53.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He met Calgara 400\Nyears ago. His name was...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.97,0:05:01.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Montblanc Noland!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.47,0:05:10.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Led by a Bell's Sound! Tale of\Nthe Great Warrior and the Explorer"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.02,0:05:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This tale took place 400 years ago,\Nand though it has never been written of,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.32,0:05:25.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it has been kept in people's hearts\Nfrom one generation to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.60,0:05:28.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is a true story of a\Nwarrior known as a monster,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.50,0:05:33.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and an adventurer known as a liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.77,0:05:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get on board, quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.04,0:05:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Monster of Shandora is coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.88,0:05:43.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry! Cast off! Cast off!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.38,0:05:50.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--B-But there are still crewmen--!\N--Just get us out to sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.49,0:05:58.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.54,0:06:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must be eliminated!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.26,0:06:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave all your belongings and go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.87,0:06:37.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Reporting, Commodore!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.87,0:06:40.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our ship's stores have finally been exhausted,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.81,0:06:46.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,meaning we're now... lost... at sea...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.21,0:06:47.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cook's fainted!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.78,0:06:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! There's no food left!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.82,0:06:53.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The commodore fell into the ocean!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.42,0:06:57.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Grand Line! Did he decide\Nto drown himself and leave us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.72,0:07:00.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he was so starved he chose death?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.56,0:07:05.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid! He's a hero who's\Nreturned twice from these waters!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.16,0:07:08.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what're these carefully\Nfolded clothes and shoes for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.00,0:07:11.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey! Someone go check...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.14,0:07:13.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Screw that! It's a sea of monsters down there!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.01,0:07:16.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not coming back up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.88,0:07:20.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Commodore!\N--Pretty nimble guy, he was. Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.01,0:07:25.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? What's this rope?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.02,0:07:29.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pull it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.19,0:07:31.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this, Commodore?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.19,0:07:33.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell us you killed it underwater?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.26,0:07:35.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cook it up for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.63,0:07:42.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really do lose your\Ntouch when you get lazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.83,0:07:44.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a huge storm, Commodore!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.84,0:07:46.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet so, given this swaying.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.01,0:07:50.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You bet so? Is that all?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.41,0:07:52.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The yardarm's been busted!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.18,0:07:54.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Where?!\N--Main! Main!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.15,0:07:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This third voyage has lasted over two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.75,0:08:03.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost miraculous it has lasted so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.99,0:08:06.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. Did you just hear something?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.19,0:08:08.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Do you mean the thunder?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.96,0:08:16.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, something beautiful, like a bell...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.07,0:08:18.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Priest! Try to keep your senses!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.97,0:08:24.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This land is cursed! At this rate,\Nthe Shandians will be wiped out!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.04,0:08:27.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-How can we save the village, Priest?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.88,0:08:32.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Offer... a girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.22,0:08:40.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the sacrificial altar!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.36,0:08:47.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How many victims does that make?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.47,0:08:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over a hundred...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.24,0:08:58.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?! This has\Nnever happened to us before!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.61,0:09:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I can be of use, I will gladly give my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.02,0:09:09.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you cry, Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.22,0:09:14.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm about to be welcomed by the sun god!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.93,0:09:22.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Being chosen to be a sacrifice\Nis a wonderful thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.80,0:09:26.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for raising me, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.94,0:09:32.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mousse!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.44,0:09:35.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this is a bad dream, let me wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.65,0:09:40.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! Go away!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.49,0:09:45.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go away!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.16,0:09:47.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great Warrior Calgara...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.49,0:09:49.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seto...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.19,0:09:53.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to be like you someday...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.20,0:10:00.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to be a brave warrior\Nand fight to protect this land!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.44,0:10:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna die because\Nof something like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.41,0:10:11.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're amazing, Commodore!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.45,0:10:15.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There really was an island in\Nthe direction you said to turn to!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.25,0:10:18.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, what a relief. We can\Nride out the storm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.46,0:10:21.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, did you guys really not hear it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.73,0:10:25.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope. None of us heard any bells. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.03,0:10:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! You must've been\Nhearing things, Commodore!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.67,0:10:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a magnificent forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.78,0:10:45.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope we find good research materials!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.99,0:10:52.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Commodore! Was that the sound you heard?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.72,0:10:55.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now! Don't tease me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.53,0:11:00.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd never mistake the sounds of\Nthis odd bird for something else!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.67,0:11:08.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Commodore! Was this--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.02,0:11:28.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow... What a beautiful tone...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.66,0:11:32.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems there are people here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.20,0:11:39.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hold on, Commodore! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.50,0:11:41.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone's lying on the ground!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.04,0:11:45.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it... Intruders!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.88,0:11:51.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Hey! Kid!\N--Commodore! This kid doesn't look right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.95,0:11:54.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.79,0:11:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let go!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.22,0:12:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Kinetsu plague.\NHe hasn't been treated at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.16,0:12:04.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-This island is bad news!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.63,0:12:06.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor! Do we have any Conine left?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.00,0:12:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inject this lad and all of us immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.74,0:12:23.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad. Even the crops\Nare being eaten away at...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.18,0:12:31.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Commodore! All the houses\Nare filled with the sick!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.98,0:13:00.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take the girl to the altar!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.23,0:13:12.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God of the sun... God of the rain...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.13,0:13:17.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God of the forest... God of the earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.37,0:13:25.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In exchange for this girl's life,\Nplease save our village!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.09,0:13:46.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Kashi God!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.03,0:13:47.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mousse!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.90,0:13:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let her go! It's for the village!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.37,0:13:56.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Kashi God has such a divine form!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.34,0:13:58.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please save my mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.71,0:14:04.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please save my son and father!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.35,0:14:06.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the--?! Something fell!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.45,0:14:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.77,0:14:27.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What on earth?! Who is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.01,0:14:29.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kashi God!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.31,0:14:37.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God-killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.18,0:14:39.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ceremony is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.52,0:14:41.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must've been really frightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.09,0:14:47.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're safe now! There's no need to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.96,0:14:52.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Kashi God! Please forgive us!\N--We're all going to be cursed!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.13,0:14:57.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kill! Give more lives to the gods!\NBefore we incur their wrath!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.24,0:15:00.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Calgara! Kill him!\N--Sounds like he did something bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.94,0:15:02.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're really freaking out!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.81,0:15:08.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--He doesn't know how to ignore!\N--He killed a god? What's that mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.28,0:15:11.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tribal rituals ain't something\Nyou mess around with!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.92,0:15:15.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quell the gods' anger,\NGreat Warrior Calgara-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.62,0:15:19.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am an explorer from\Nthe North Blue, Montblanc--
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.22,0:15:24.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter who you are!\NYou must be eliminated!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.50,0:15:29.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this how you've eliminated all\Nthe few, yet vital advancements?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.20,0:15:34.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're in no place to criticize!\NAtone to the gods where you stand!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.14,0:15:42.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is that man?! He's holding\Nhis own against Calgara!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.48,0:15:50.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There! Use that knife to take your life!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.49,0:15:51.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.92,0:15:56.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A sacrifice meant to save the village,\Ncrying because she wants to live...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.33,0:16:01.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you no shame?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.50,0:16:05.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be a fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.07,0:16:13.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.25,0:16:28.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Commodore!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.39,0:16:31.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For centuries we've strictly\Nupheld the commandment
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.96,0:16:35.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that all intruders on this\Nisland must be punished!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.07,0:16:39.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, you're a god-killer!\NYou, alone, won't be enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.07,0:16:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You and all your men will pay with your lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.68,0:16:50.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Lives" this, "sacrifices" that!\NWill those make your gods happy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.58,0:16:52.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These ceremonies are flat-out denials
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.58,0:16:58.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of the triumphs of all the great men\Nbefore us! I won't stand for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.16,0:17:01.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is an insult to all the\Nadventurers and researchers
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.83,0:17:07.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who've ever set out to sea in the\Nhopes of bringing people happiness!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.40,0:17:10.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If your gods value people's lives,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.34,0:17:17.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then wouldn't they have contempt\Nfor these ceremonies, too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.01,0:17:21.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me time!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.85,0:17:25.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll banish this so-called curse of yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.48,0:17:30.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if I can't, you can do whatever you like!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.89,0:17:32.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.12,0:17:36.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think you're a god or something?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.13,0:17:40.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In return, if I do save this village from tragedy,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.63,0:17:44.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,swear to me you'll never\Nhold these ceremonies again!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.67,0:17:46.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all you have to say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.67,0:17:50.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such nonsense! Now you die!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.07,0:17:52.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Try it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.91,0:17:55.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Eh?!\N--What are you saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.01,0:18:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These people have until\Ntomorrow evening to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.89,0:18:07.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.06,0:18:13.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's "goodbye, world" come sunset tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.13,0:18:15.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have faith in the commodore!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.17,0:18:19.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, girlie. I feel bad for you too;\Nyou were born in this village...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.94,0:18:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! With your looks,\Nyou could marry an aristocrat!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.01,0:18:26.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Knock it off, guys! Don't you have any tact?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.95,0:18:28.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.48,0:18:31.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you mean the commodore?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.98,0:18:37.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's Montblanc Noland,\Na renowned explorer. And a botanist.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.79,0:18:42.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He visits uncharted islands and finds\Nand researches new plants there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.96,0:18:45.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's pretty much a hero back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.70,0:18:48.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he's too good-natured...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.17,0:18:51.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And his biggest flaw is that\Nhe can't ignore stuff like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.37,0:18:55.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We do trust him, though!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.61,0:18:58.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you let Calgara kill him there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.01,0:19:02.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The answer will make itself known tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.15,0:19:06.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He says he can save our village.\NThere is no harm in waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.45,0:19:08.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you be so carefree?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.35,0:19:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll listen to him, but not\Nthe priest's last words?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.69,0:19:16.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calgara! Say something!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.69,0:19:19.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I sense the village is in\Neven the slightest danger,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.40,0:19:24.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take that man's head without\Nwaiting for tomorrow's sun to set.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.97,0:19:28.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do not have the power\Nto hear the gods' voices.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.97,0:19:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I do know when a man is\Nspeaking earnest words. That is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.49,0:19:45.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should you really be up?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.39,0:19:48.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm all better...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.63,0:19:51.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great Warrior Calgara...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.63,0:19:59.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does "advancement" mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.78,0:20:07.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we are! A Cona tree!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.35,0:20:15.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd be surprised if there wasn't\None in such a big forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.85,0:20:18.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Earthquake!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.59,0:20:25.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--It's happening! It's really happening!\N--It's the Kashi God's curse!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.70,0:20:33.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let us out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.88,0:20:44.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad... The forest floor has sunk...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.55,0:20:52.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like the island is about to tear apart!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.26,0:20:59.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looking good!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.36,0:21:05.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems the gods have given a\Ncrushing blow to you directly!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.40,0:21:10.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, these gods...\Naren't that great... at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.71,0:21:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They don't even have the strength...\Nto kill a single person...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.22,0:21:20.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're stubborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.25,0:21:26.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but could you get lost?\NI don't feel like looking at you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.56,0:21:30.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... must hurry to the village!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.26,0:21:34.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amusing. I think I'll see this through.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.57,0:21:40.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just try and squirm out!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.17,0:21:45.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're feeling lonely, talk to me
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.68,0:21:50.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You gaze at the heavens\Nas you wander about
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.78,0:21:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like the moon,\Nyou keep your gaze constant
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.66,0:22:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And your deep reflection wanes\Nas you slowly disappear
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.84,0:22:18.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay as you are, let those words guide you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.02,0:22:33.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dream, you travelers who spend\Ncountless nights drifting
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.10,0:22:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you may not be able to go back
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.53,0:22:50.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you will surely start moving forward again
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.31,0:23:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How unsightly! Is this the wreck\Nof a man who defied the gods?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.89,0:23:05.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will your village die by curse, or by disease?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.49,0:23:08.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Are you that afraid of your gods?!\N--Don't talk like you understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.19,0:23:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However great your gods are,\Npeople's lives are even more precious!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.20,0:23:13.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next episode of One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.53,0:23:16.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Free from the Spell!\NThe Great Warrior Sheds Tears!!"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.73,0:23:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
